= Findings and Discussion

== Introduction

This chapter presents and interprets the empirical results generated by the multimodal M&A synergy prediction pipeline. The chapter is structured around three axes. Section 4.2 reports the model ablation ladder, establishing the headline predictive performance of each configuration and grounding the discussion in real cross-validated metrics. Section 4.3 addresses each of the three hypotheses in turn — topological alpha (H1), semantic divergence (H2), and topological arbitrage (H3) — using both quantitative evidence and interpretive commentary. Section 4.4 discusses the SHAP decomposition as the evidentiary bridge between predictive performance and economic credibility. Section 4.5 confronts the principal limitations of the findings honestly. Section 4.6 synthesises the chapter's contribution before the conclusion.

All results reported below derive from five-fold stratified cross-validation on the final assembled dataset. The primary evaluation metric is AUC-ROC, with Accuracy and F1 reported as secondary diagnostics. All preprocessing — median imputation and StandardScaler normalisation — was fit exclusively on training folds and applied forward to held-out folds, guaranteeing zero forward-looking data leakage @mackinlay1997 @creswell2014.

== Model Ablation Results

=== The Performance Ladder

Three feature configurations were evaluated across three classifier families (Logistic Regression, XGBoost, and MLP), producing a structured ablation ladder that isolates the marginal contribution of each modality. @tbl-ablation reports the best-performing classifier per configuration, which in every case is XGBoost.

